Task 1: Attack Surface & Types of Attackers:

Attack Surface:
    *An attack surface is the total number of entry points through which an attacker can attempt to compromise a system.
  Common Attack Surfaces
    *Web applications (login pages, forms)
    *Mobile applications
    *APIs
    *Networks (Wi-Fi, routers)
    *Cloud infrastructure
    *Databases

Script Kiddies:
  *Beginners using ready-made tools without deep knowledge.
Insiders:
  *Employees misusing authorized access.
Hacktivists:	
  *Attack for political or social causes
Cyber Criminals:	
  *Motivated by financial gain
Nation-State Actors:
  *Government-backed attackers targeting critical infrastructure
